Defining Kirsch Relations

In [ ]:
#Radial Stress/Po
def sig_rr(ratio, k, theta):
  sigrr = (1/2)*(1+k)*(1-(ratio**2)) - (1/2)*(1-k)*(1 + 3*(ratio**4) - 4*(ratio**2))*math.cos(2*theta)
  return(sigrr)

#Tangential Stress/Po
def sig_tt(ratio, k, theta):
  sigtt = (1/2)*(1+k)*(1+(ratio**2)) + (1/2)*(1-k)*(1 + 3*((ratio**4)))*math.cos(2*theta)
  return(sigtt)

#Shear Stress/Po
def sig_rt(ratio, k, theta):
  sigrt = (1/2)*(1-k)*(1-3*(ratio**4) + 2*(ratio**2))*math.sin(2*theta)
  return(sigrt)

Range of r/a Values taken from 1 to 5 with increment value of 0.001. Similarly values of k was taken from 0 to 1 with increment value of 0.3

ratio_inverse = np.arange(1,5,0.0001)

k = np.arange(0,1,0.3)

Case 1 : Stress Distribution for Multiple Openings Theta_A = 0 & Theta_B = 180

Defining theta values

In [ ]:
theta_a = math.radians(0)
theta_b = math.radians(180)

Defining Values of Radial & Tangential Stress

In [80]:
sig_rr_values = [[0 for j in range(k.size)] for i in range(ratio_inverse.size)]
sig_tt_values = [[0 for j in range(k.size)] for i in range(ratio_inverse.size)]

for j in range(k.size):
  for i in range(ratio_inverse.size):
    a_by_r_circle1 = 1/ratio_inverse[i]
    a_by_r_circle2 = 1/ratio_inverse[ratio_inverse.size-i - 1]
    sig_tt_values[i][j] = sig_tt(a_by_r_circle1, k[j], theta_a) + sig_tt(a_by_r_circle2, k[j], theta_b)
  
    sig_rr_values[i][j] = sig_rr(a_by_r_circle1,k[j], theta_a) + sig_rr(a_by_r_circle2, k[j], theta_b)
In [ ]:
from matplotlib.pyplot import figure

fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=2, ncols=2, figsize=(15,15))
for i, ax in enumerate(axes.flat, start=1):
    ax.set_title('Stress Distribution for Theta  = 0 and k = {}'.format(k[i-1]))
    sig_tt_vals =  [row[i-1] for row in sig_tt_values]
    sig_rr_vals =  [row[i-1] for row in sig_rr_values]
    ax.plot(ratio_inverse,sig_tt_vals)
    ax.plot(ratio_inverse, sig_rr_vals)
    ax.set_xlabel('r/a value')
    ax.set_ylabel('Tangential Stress/Po || Radial Stress/Po')
    ax.legend(['Tangential Sress/Po','Radial Stress/Po'])

fig.tight_layout()
plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
# Define limits of coordinate system
x1 = -4
x2 = 9
y1 = -2
y2 = 4

circle1 = plt.Circle((0,0),1, color = 'k', fill = False, clip_on = False)
circle2 = plt.Circle((6,0),1, color='k', fill = False, clip_on = False)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15,12))
ax.add_artist(circle1)
ax.add_artist(circle2)
plt.axis("equal")
ax.spines['left'].set_position('zero')
ax.spines['bottom'].set_position('zero')
ax.spines['right'].set_color('none')
ax.spines['top'].set_color('none')
ax.xaxis.set_ticks_position('bottom')
ax.yaxis.set_ticks_position('left')
sig_tt_vals =  [row[3] for row in sig_tt_values]
sig_rr_vals =  [row[3] for row in sig_rr_values]
ax.plot(ratio_inverse,sig_tt_vals)
ax.plot(ratio_inverse, sig_rr_vals)
plt.xlim(left=x1)
plt.xlim(right=x2)
plt.ylim(bottom=y1)
plt.ylim(top=y2)
ax.legend(['Tangential Sress/Po','Radial Stress/Po'], fontsize=15)
plt.axhline(linewidth=1, color='k')
plt.axvline(linewidth=1, color='k')
plt.grid(color='k', linestyle='-.', linewidth=0.5)
plt.title('Stress Distribution for ThetaA = 0 & ThetaB = 180 and k = 0.8999', fontsize=20)
plt.xlabel('r/a Value', fontsize=15)
plt.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np
# Define limits of coordinate system
x1 = -8
x2 = 8
y1 = -2
y2 = 8

circle1 = plt.Circle((0,0),1, color = 'k', fill = False, clip_on = False)
circle2 = plt.Circle((0,6),1, color='k', fill = False, clip_on = False)
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(15,15))
ax.add_artist(circle1)
ax.add_artist(circle2)
plt.axis("equal")
ax.spines['left'].set_position('zero')
ax.spines['bottom'].set_position('zero')
ax.spines['right'].set_color('black')
ax.spines['top'].set_color('none')
ax.xaxis.set_ticks_position('bottom')
ax.yaxis.set_ticks_position('left')

sig_rr_vals_k1 = [row[0] for row in sig_rr_values_case2]
sig_rr_vals_k2 = [row[1] for row in sig_rr_values_case2]
sig_rr_vals_k3 = [row[2] for row in sig_rr_values_case2]
sig_rr_vals_k4 = [row[3] for row in sig_rr_values_case2]
ax.plot(sig_rr_vals_k1, ratio_inverse, label = round(k[0],3))
ax.plot(sig_rr_vals_k2, ratio_inverse, label = round(k[1],3))
ax.plot(sig_rr_vals_k3, ratio_inverse, label = round(k[2],3))
ax.plot(sig_rr_vals_k4, ratio_inverse, label = round(k[3],3))

plt.xlim(left=x1)
plt.xlim(right=x2)
plt.ylim(bottom=y1)
plt.ylim(top=y2)
plt.axhline(linewidth=1, color='k')
plt.axvline(linewidth=1, color='k')
plt.grid(color='k', linestyle='-.', linewidth=0.5)
plt.legend(title = 'k-values')
plt.title('Radial Stress Distribution for ThetaA = 90 & ThetaB = 270 & Diff k-values', fontsize=20)
plt.xlabel('Radial_Stress/Po --->', fontsize=10)
plt.show()
